      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p><!-- BIOGHIST REQUIRED -->Professor of Government 1943-1948, Provost 1949-1950 and
            President 1953-1968, Columbia University.</p>
         <p/>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content</head>
         <p>The collection containd correspondence, memoranda, drafts, committee meeting reports
            relevant to the operation of Columbia University, including the gymnasium, faculty
            members and real estate holdings on Morningside Heights and elsewhere. Also included are
            books from his library.</p>
         <p/>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Collection is arranged into three series <list type="marked">
                    <item>Series I: Topical
                  Office Files, 1958-1984</item>
                    <item>Series II: Correspondence,
                  1968</item>
                    <item>Series III: Books from Kirk's Library</item>
                </list>
            </p>
      </arrangement>
